            . I am a <rs id="t18300114-197-viclabel1051" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300114-197-victim1326 t18300114-197-viclabel1051"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300114-197-crimeloc1052">Hackney-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300114-197-crimeloc1052" type="placeName" value="Hackney-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300114-197-crimeloc1052" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300114-197-off1049 t18300114-197-crimeloc1052"></join>. On the 19th of December, about four o'clock, I lost a piece of Scotch sheeting from the step of my door - I had seen it in the morning; this is it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. LEE. Q. Are you in a large way of business? A.Not particularly so; here is the private mark on it, made with my own hands.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300114-197-person1328">
                  JOHN 
                  MATAULE
               <interp inst="t18300114-197-person1328" type="surname" value="MATAULE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300114-197-person1328" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300114-197-person1328" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a waiter at the Durham Arms. I saw the prisoner and two others walking by the shop; I saw the prisoner take this cloth from the step of the door under his arm; he carried it across the road, and put it on his shoulder - he went down another street; I and Mr. Sexton went after him - we met him and his companions with the cloth; I carried the cloth to the officer's house.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you known him before? A. No, but I had seen him the day previous; I was carrying the porter out when I saw him - it was rather darkish.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300114-197-person1329">
                  JOHN 
                  MAUNDER
               <interp inst="t18300114-197-person1329" type="surname" value="MAUNDER"></interp>
